    "_postman_id": "sc2-tbm-100k-001",
    "name": "StableCoin-TreasuryBacked-MultiContract-100K-30d",
    "description": "ACTUS: TREASURY-BACKED MULTI-CONTRACT SIMULATION ($100K Reserve)\n\nGAP ADDRESSED: §11.1 — All existing simulations model a SINGLE PAM contract.\nThis simulation models the RESERVE SIDE with MULTIPLE T-bill contracts\nrunning simultaneously alongside the stablecoin liability.\n\nCORE THESIS: A stablecoin can be 103% BACKED but only 1.1% LIQUID.\nThis simulation proves it by modeling the maturity ladder explicitly.\n\n5 ACTUS Contracts:\n  TBill-A-100K (PAM, $24,500, matures Mar 15) — 4-week\n  TBill-B-100K (PAM, $24,500, matures Mar 30) — 8-week\n  TBill-C-100K (PAM, $24,500, matures Apr 15) — 13-week\n  TBill-D-100K (PAM, $24,500, matures Apr 30) — 13-week\n  StableCoin-100K-Liability (PAM, $100,000 supply)\n\nMATURITY LADDER shows cash inflows:\n  Day 15 (Mar 15): +$24,500 from T-Bill A → cash spike\n  Day 30 (Mar 30): +$24,500 from T-Bill B → cash spike\n\nBehavioral Models: BackingRatio + RedemptionPressure + MaturityLadder\nMarket Risk: T-bill mark-to-market via SC_TBILL_MV reference index\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
